{{Infobox Hollywood cartoon| | cartoon_name = Felix in Hollywood | series = [[Felix the Cat]] | image = felix-chaplin.jpg | caption = Felix and Charlie Chaplin share the screen in a memorable moment from the short. | director = [[Otto Messmer]] | story_artist = | animator = | voice_actor = | musician = | producer = [[Pat Sullivan (film producer)|Pat Sullivan]] | studio = Pat Sullivan Studios | distributor = [[Margaret J. Winkler]] | release_date = July 15, 1923 | color_process = Black and white | runtime = 9 min. 17 sec. | movie_language = [[English language|English]] | preceded_by = "Felix Strikes it Rich" | followed_by = "Felix in Fairyland" }}
'''''Felix in Hollywood''''' is a 1923 short featuring [[Felix the Cat]]. In the episode, Felix goes to [[Hollywood]] and meets [[Charlie Chaplin]], [[Douglas Fairbanks]], [[William S. Hart]], [[Cecil B. DeMille]], [[Will H. Hays|Will Hays]], [[Snub Pollard]] & [[Ben Turpin]], in the first animated cartoon to feature caricatures of Hollywood celebrities.
==Reception== It was named #50 of [[The 50 Greatest Cartoons]] of all time in a 1994 survey of animators and cartoon historians by [[Jerry Beck]],<ref>{{cite book|title=The 50 Greatest Cartoons: As Selected by 1,000 Animation Professionals|author=Jerry Beck, ed.|year=1998|publisher=JG Press, Inc.|isbn=1-57215-271-0}}</ref> making it the only Felix the Cat cartoon on the list.
