'''Mamadie Touré''' is the widow of [[Lansana Conté]], the former president of [[Guinea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://panamapapers.icij.org/the_power_players/|title=The Power Players|publisher=|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/5e2a55a0-756c-11e4-b1bf-00144feabdc0.html#axzz44oQ5nusz|title=US prosecutors show their hand in Guinea corruption probe|work=Financial Times|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.globalwitness.org/en/archive/damning-video-and-contracts-show-bsgr-was-lying-guinea-mining-scandal/|title=Damning video and contracts show BSGR was lying in Guinea mining scandal|work=Global Witness|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/apr/16/fbi-arrest-bribery-10bn-mountain|title=FBI arrest agent over bribery cover up claim in battle over $10bn mountain|author=Ian Cobain|work=the Guardian|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://guineenews.org/feuilleton-simandou-le-corrupteur-de-mamadie-toure-expulse-par-les-etats-unis/|title=Feuilleton Simandou – Le «corrupteur de Mamadie Touré» expulsé par les Etats-Unis|work=Guinéenews|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref>

Her name appears in numerous investigations into the activities of Pentler Holdings, who is said to have transferred through a network of shell companies at least one payment of $2.4 million US -- with more pledged -- to her [[offshore company]], Matinda, in return for her help obtaining a concession in [[Simandou mine]] from her husband shortly before his death.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/africa/2016/04/04/Panama-Papers-Steinmetz-Guinea-deal-pried-open |title=Panama Papers: Steinmetz Guinea deal pried open |author=KHADIJA SHARIFE |date= April 4, 2016 |accessdate=May 9, 2016|publisher=Times Live |work=#Panama Papers}}</ref>

