This is a timeline of major events in 2018 related to the investigations into [[links between Trump associates and Russian officials|links between associates]] of [[Donald Trump]] and Russian officials that are suspected of being inappropriate. It follows the [[timeline of Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections]] and the [[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (2017)|timeline of investigations in 2017]], and precedes that of [[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (2019)|2019]].
== Relevant individuals and organizations == {{transcluded-section|Timeline of Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections}} {{#section-h::Timeline of Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections|Relevant individuals and organizations}}
== 2018 == === January === * '''January''': Federal agents photograph Maria Butina dining with Oleg Zhiganov, the director of the [[Russian Cultural Center]]. Zhiganov is expelled from the U.S. in March for being a suspected Russian spy. In a July hearing, prosecutors offer Butina's association with Zhiganov as one reason she should be considered a [[Bail in the United States|flight risk]] and denied bail.<ref>{{cite web|title=Accused Russian agent met with suspected Kremlin spy|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/07/28/mariia-butina-russia-kremlin-suspected-spy-746043|website=[[Politico]]|date=July 28, 2018|access-date=August 1, 2018|last=Meyer|first=Josh}}</ref> * '''January 2''': In a ''New York Times'' op-ed, Fusion GPS founders Glenn Simpson and Peter Fritsch request that congressional [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]] "release full transcripts of our firm’s testimony" and add that "the Steele dossier was not the trigger for the FBI’s investigation into Russian meddling." Their sources said the dossier was taken seriously because it corroborated reports from other sources, "including one inside the Trump camp."<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/02/opinion/republicans-investigation-fusion-gps.html |title=The Republicans’ Fake Investigations|last1=Simpson|first1=Glenn R.|last2=Fritsch|first2=Peter|date=January 2, 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=January 3, 2018}}</ref> * '''January 3''': ** Manafort files a lawsuit challenging Mueller's broad authority and alleging the DoJ violated the law in appointing Mueller.<ref name=cnn-20180103>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2018/01/03/politics/manafort-lawsuit-robert-mueller-authority/index.html |title=Manafort sues Mueller in Russia probe |last=Perez |first=Evan |publisher=[[CNN]] |date=January 3, 2018 |access-date=January 3, 2018}}</ref> A department spokesperson replies that "the lawsuit is frivolous but the defendant is entitled to file whatever he wants."<ref name=cnn-20180103 /> ** CNN reports that Trump's legal team held talks with Mueller's team a few days before Christmas.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2018/01/02/politics/trump-lawyers-special-counsel/index.html |title=Trump lawyers talked with special counsel team |last=Perez |first=Evan |date=January 2, 2018 |work=CNN|access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref> ** Rosenstein and Wray meet with Ryan about the House Russia investigation.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://thehill.com/homenews/house/367314-rosenstein-meeting-with-paul-ryan-about-russia-investigation |title=Rosenstein meets with Ryan about Russia investigation |last=Seipel |first=Brooke |date=January 3, 2018 |work=The Hill|access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref> ** Excerpts from ''[[Fire and Fury]]'', a forthcoming book by [[Michael Wolff (journalist)|Michael Wolff]], are published, in which Bannon describes Trump Jr's [[Trump Tower meeting|meeting with Natalia Veselnitskaya]] as "treasonous" and "unpatriotic". Wolff's book also describes Bannon's confidence that Trump Sr. knew of the meeting at the time. Trump subsequently tweets that Bannon had "very little to do with our historic victory" and that he has "lost his mind".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/bannon-trump-book-russia-claims-bad-news-president-cost-dearly-a8140691.html |title=Trump trusted Bannon the most, and that could now cost him very dearly |date=January 3, 2018 |work=The Independent|access-date=January 6, 2018 |language=en-GB|last=Buncombe|first=Andrew}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/steve-bannon-calls-trump-tower-russian-meeting-treasonous-new-book-n834286 |title=Steve Bannon calls Trump Tower Russian meeting 'treasonous' in new book |work=NBC News|access-date=January 6, 2018 |language=en|date=January 3, 2018|last=Clark|first=Dartunorro}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2018/01/steve-bannon-is-trumps-frankenstein-monster/549566/ |title=Steve Bannon Is Trump's Frankenstein Monster |last=Graham |first=David A. |work=The Atlantic|access-date=January 6, 2018 |language=en-US|date=January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nypost.com/2018/01/03/bannon-trump-jr-meeting-with-russians-was-treasonous/ |title=Bannon: Trump Jr. meeting with Russians was ‘treasonous’ |date=January 3, 2018 |work=New York Post|access-date=January 6, 2018 |language=en-US|last=Moore|first=Mark}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/03/donald-trump-russia-steve-bannon-michael-wolff |title=Trump Tower meeting with Russians 'treasonous', Bannon says in explosive book |last=Smith |first=David |date=January 3, 2018 |work=The Guardian|access-date=January 6, 2018 |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> ** Trump lawyers send Bannon a letter demanding that he refrain from making disparaging comments against Trump and his family.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/trump-attorney-sends-bannon-cease-desist-letter-disparaging/story?id=52128555 |title=Trump attorney sends Bannon cease and desist letter over 'disparaging' comments |last=Santucci |first=John |date=January 3, 2018 |website=ABC News|access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-lawyers-send-cease-and-desist-letter-to-bannon/2018/01/03/b4d1ad7e-f0ff-11e7-97bf-bba379b809ab_story.html |title=Trump’s lawyers send cease-and-desist letter to Bannon |last=Leonnig |first=Carol D. |date=January 3, 2018 |work=Washington Post|access-date=January 4, 2018 |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286}}</ref> As a consequence, ''Fire and Fury''<nowiki/>'s publication date is advanced to January 5.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * '''January 4''': ** ''The New York Times'' reports that two days after Comey's congressional testimony, an aide to Sessions approached a Capitol Hill staff member to ask for any derogatory information about Comey. Sessions purportedly wanted one negative article about Comey per day in the news media.<ref name=nyt-20180104>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/04/us/politics/trump-sessions-russia-mcgahn.html |title=Obstruction Inquiry Shows Trump’s Struggle to Keep Grip on Russia Investigation |last=Schmidt |first=Michael S. |author-link=Michael S. Schmidt |date=January 4, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=January 5, 2018}}</ref> ** Mueller has handwritten notes from Priebus that show that Trump talked to Priebus about how he had called Comey to urge him to say publicly that Trump was not under investigation.<ref name=nyt-20180104 /> ** CNN reports that [[The Trump Organization]] has provided Mueller and Congressional investigators with documents on a wide range of events, including conversations and meetings about Trump's real estate business.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2018/01/04/politics/trump-organization-documents-robert-mueller-russia-investigators/index.html?sr=fbCNN010418trump-organization-documents-robert-mueller-russia-investigators0210PMVODtopLink |title=Trump Organization gave Russia-related documents to Mueller, Capitol Hill|first1=Cristina|last1=Alesci|first2=Pamela|last2=Brown|work=CNN|access-date=April 11, 2018|date=January 4, 2018}}</ref> ** A federal judge denies Fusion GPS's bid to prevent the House Intelligence Committee from obtaining the firm's bank records.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/01/04/fusion-gps-house-intel-records-325396 |title=Judge: House panel entitled to Fusion GPS bank records |date=January 4, 2018 |work=Politico|access-date=January 5, 2018|last=Gerstein|first=Josh}}</ref> * '''January 5''': Grassley and Graham make the first criminal referral of the congressional investigations, recommending that the DoJ investigate Steele for potentially making false statements to the FBI "regarding his distribution of information contained in the dossier".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/senior-republican-refers-trump-dossier-author-for-possible-charges/2018/01/05/ead4585e-f0af-11e7-b390-a36dc3fa2842_story.html |title=Senior Republican refers Trump-Russia dossier author for possible charges |last1=Barrett |first1=Devlin |date=January 5, 2018 |work=Washington Post|access-date=January 5, 2018 |last2=Hamburger |first2=Tom |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url-access=subscription|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/senators-ask-justice-department-to-open-criminal-probe-into-trump-dossier-author-1515180982 |title=Senators Ask Justice Department to Open Criminal Probe Into Trump Dossier Author |last=Tau |first=Byron |date=January 5, 2018 |work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=January 5, 2018 |language=en-US |issn=0099-9660}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/former-british-spy-christopher-steele-named-in-first-criminal-referral-of-us-russia-probe-11196828 |title=Former British spy Christopher Steele named in first criminal referral of US Russia probe |work=Sky News |date=January 5, 2018}}</ref> * '''January 6''': CNN reports that Spicer, Priebus and McGahn all tried to pressure Sessions not to recuse himself in the FBI's Russia Investigation, which ultimately led to Rosenstein appointing Mueller as special counsel.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2018/01/05/politics/reince-priebus-sean-spicer-sessions-recusal/index.html |title=Others involved in effort to pressure Sessions to not recuse |last=Acosta |first=Jim |date=January 6, 2018 |work=CNN|access-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref> * '''January 7''': Senate Judiciary Committee members [[Richard Blumenthal]] (D-CT) and [[Sheldon Whitehouse]] (D-RI) write to Grassley, demanding the publication of the Fusion GPS testimony of August 22, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thehill.com/homenews/senate/367927-senate-dems-demand-release-of-fusion-gps-interview |title=Senate Dems demand release of Fusion GPS interview |website=The Hill |date=January 8, 2018|last=Shelbourne|first=Mallory|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/senate-democrats-call-on-chuck-grassley-to-release-fusion-gps-interview/article/2645276 |title=Senate Democrats call on Chuck Grassley to release Fusion GPS interview |website=The Washington Examiner |date=January 8, 2018|last=Cohen|first=Kelly|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref><ref name=SimpsonHouseIntelTranscript20171104>[[s:Senate Judiciary Committee Interview of Glenn Simpson]]</ref>
[[File:PUTIN’S ASYMMETRIC ASSAULT ON DEMOCRACY IN RUSSIA AND EUROPE.pdf|thumb|Putin's Asymmetric Assault on Democracy in Russia and Europe: Implications for U.S. National Security]] * '''January 9''': ** Feinstein unilaterally releases the transcript of the Fusion GPS testimony given to the Senate Judiciary Committee on August 22, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/01/09/feinstein-releases-transcript-of-interview-with-fusion-gps-co-founder-329573 |title='Human source' in Trump orbit contacted FBI, Fusion GPS co-founder told senators|last=Cheney|first=Kyle|date=January 9, 2018|work=Politico|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref> ** ''The Daily Beast'' reports that a senior National Security Council official proposed withdrawing some U.S. military forces from Eastern Europe as an overture to Putin during the Trump administration's early days.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/white-house-official-floated-withdrawing-us-forces-to-please-putin |title=White House Official Floated Withdrawing U.S. Forces to Please Putin |last=Ackerman |first=Spencer |date=January 10, 2018 |work=The Daily Beast|access-date=January 10, 2018}}</ref> ** Trump's personal attorney [[Michael D. Cohen (lawyer)|Michael Cohen]] sues [[BuzzFeed]] and [[Fusion GPS]] for [[defamation]] over allegations about him in a [[Trump–Russia dossier|dossier]] the news organization published that was commissioned in 2016 by Trump's political opponents.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-01-10/trump-lawyer-cohen-sues-buzzfeed-over-claims-in-russia-dossier |title=Trump Lawyer Sues BuzzFeed, Fusion GPS on Russia Dossier Claims|date=January 10, 2018 |work=Bloomberg.com|access-date=April 11, 2018|last=Jacobs|first=Jennifer}}</ref> ** FBI agents subpoena Bannon to appear before a grand jury.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/bannon-plans-cooperate-special-counsel-russia-probe-source-says-n838271 |title=FBI agents visited Steve Bannon’s home last week to discuss subpoena in Russia probe |work=NBC News|language=en|last1=Jackson|first1=Hallie|last2=Welker|first2=Kristen|last3=Ainsley|first3=Julia|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref> * '''January 10''': ** ''The Washington Post'' reports that Mueller has added a veteran cyber prosecutor, Ryan K. Dickey, to his team, filling what has long been a gap in expertise and potentially signaling a recent focus on [[Cybercrime|computer crimes]]. Dickey was previously assigned to the DoJ [[Computer Crime and Intellectual Property Section]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/mueller-adds-veteran-cyber-prosecutor-to-special-counsel-team/2018/01/10/860f3364-f585-11e7-b34a-b85626af34ef_story.html |title=Mueller adds veteran cyber prosecutor to special-counsel team |last=Zapotosky |first=Matt |date=January 10, 2018 |work=Washington Post|access-date=January 10, 2018 |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286}}</ref> ** The United States Senate Foreign Relations Committee releases a report, "Putin's Asymmetric Assault on Democracy in Russia and Europe: Implications for U.S. National Security."<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cardin.senate.gov/newsroom/press/release/us-senator-ben-cardin-releases-report-detailing-two-decades-of-putins-attacks-on-democracy-calling-for-policy-changes-to-counter-kremlin-threat-ahead-of-2018-2020-elections |title=U.S. Senator Ben Cardin Releases Report Detailing Two Decades of Putin’s Attacks on Democracy, Calling for Policy Changes to Counter Kremlin Threat Ahead of 2018, 2020 Elections|author=U.S. Senator Ben Cardin of Maryland|website=www.cardin.senate.gov|language=en|access-date=January 17, 2018}}</ref> ** In a refiling of a 2008 suit filed in the [[Cayman Islands]], Deripaska sues Manafort and Gates in [[Judiciary of New York (state)|New York state court]] for over $25 million in [[damages]]. Deripaska alleges that Mueller's indictments of Manafort and Gates provide new information in the case.<ref>{{cite web|title=Russian oligarch Oleg Deripaska sues Manafort and Gates in N.Y.|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/russian-oligarch-oleg-deripaska-sues-manafort-gates-ny-n836586|website=[[NBC News]]|date=January 10, 2018|access-date=July 3, 2018|last1=Dilanian|first1=Ken|last2=Winter|first2=Tom}}</ref> * '''Week of January 15''': Mueller's team interviews [[Jeff Sessions]].<ref name=MuellerInterviewsPompeoTheGuardian20180124>{{cite web|title=CIA chief Mike Pompeo interviewed in Mueller's Russia investigation – report|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/24/cia-director-mike-pompeo-mueller-trump-russia|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=January 24, 2018|access-date=March 27, 2018|author=Staff and agencies}}</ref> * '''January 16''': Bannon testifies to the House Intelligence Committee,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/News/steve-bannon-expected-meet-house-intel-committee/story?id=52359787 |title=Steve Bannon expected to meet with House Intel Committee |last1=Siegel|first1=Benjamin|last2=Palmeri|first2=Tara|last3=Dukakis|first3=Ali|date=January 16, 2018 |website=ABC News|access-date=January 16, 2018}}</ref> and remains tight-lipped, citing [[executive privilege]].<ref name=woodruff-20180117 /> He indicates he will not invoke privilege when he testifies before Mueller's grand jury.<ref name=woodruff-20180117>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/steve-bannon-will-tell-all-to-robert-mueller-source-says |title=Steve Bannon Will Tell All to Robert Mueller, Source Says |last=Woodruff |first=Betsy |date=January 17, 2018 |work=The Daily Beast|access-date=January 17, 2018}}</ref> The next day, [[Axios (website)|Axios]] reports that Bannon informed the Committee that he had had a discussion with Priebus, Spicer, and Corallo about the June 2016 Veselnitskaya meeting.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.axios.com/steve-bannon-congress-testimony-inside-room-e30bd797-3720-44f0-bf32-5760cb6882e9.html |title=Inside the room: What Steve Bannon told Congress |date=January 17, 2018 |publisher=Axios|last=Swan|first=Jonathan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/01/17/bannon-talked-with-priebus-spicer-about-trump-tower-meeting-axios.html |title=Bannon reportedly told House panel he talked to Priebus, Spicer about June 2016 Trump Tower meeting with Russians |date=January 17, 2018 |publisher=CNBC|last=Breuninger|first=Kevin}}</ref> * '''January 17''': ** Lewandowski<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/lewandowski-rebuffs-house-committee-s-questions-russia-probe-n838626 |title=Lewandowski rebuffs House committee’s questions in Russia probe |work=NBC News|access-date=January 18, 2018 |language=en|last=Memoli|first=Mike|date=January 17, 2018}}</ref> and Dearborn testify before the House Intelligence Committee's investigators.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-01-17/lewandowski-dearborn-to-testify-amid-executive-privilege-flap |title=Lewandowski Declines to Answer Some House Panel Questions |date=January 17, 2018 |work=Bloomberg.com|access-date=January 18, 2018|last=House|first=Billy}}</ref> ** ''BuzzFeed News'' reports that Mueller's team and Senate Intelligence Committee investigators are looking into hundreds of financial transactions flagged as suspicious between the Russian government and people in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=Investigators Are Scrutinizing Newly Uncovered Payments By The Russian Embassy|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/jasonleopold/newly-uncovered-russian-payments-are-a-focus-of-election|website=[[BuzzFeed News]]|date=January 17, 2018|access-date=August 2, 2018|last1=Leopold|first1=Jason|author-link1=Jason Leopold|last2=Cormier|first2=Anthony|last3=Loop|first3=Emma|last4=Kozyreva|first4=Tanya}}</ref> * '''January 18''': ** McClatchy reports that the FBI is investigating whether the [[Central Bank of Russia|Central Bank of Russia's]] deputy governor, [[Alexander Torshin]], funneled money to the Trump campaign through the NRA.<ref name=RussiaNRAMcClatchy20180118>{{Cite news |url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/national/article195231139.html |title=FBI investigating whether Russian money went to NRA to help Trump |publisher=McClatchy DC |date=January 18, 2018|last1=Stone|first1=Peter|last2=Gordon|first2=Greg|access-date=March 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/plum-line/wp/2018/01/18/the-russia-scandal-just-got-bigger-and-republicans-are-trying-to-prevent-an-accounting/?hpid=hp_no-name_opinion-card-c%3Ahomepage%2Fstory |title=The Russia scandal just got bigger. And Republicans are trying to prevent an accounting. |work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=January 18, 2018|last=Waldman|first=Paul |access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref> ** The House Intelligence Committee releases the transcript of the Glenn Simpson testimony given on November 14, 2017.<ref name="auto6">{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2018/01/18/house-panel-releases-glenn-simpson-testimony-transcript.html |title=House panel releases Glenn Simpson testimony transcript |date=January 18, 2018 |publisher=Fox News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2018/01/18/house-intelligence-committee-votes-to-release-transcript-interview-with-fusion-gps-boss.html |title=House Intelligence Committee votes to release transcript of interview with Fusion GPS boss |last=Singman |first=Brooke |date=January 18, 2018 |work=Fox News|access-date=January 19, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> Schiff says the testimony contains "serious allegations that [[the Trump Organization]] may have engaged in [[money laundering]] with Russian nationals". Trump Organization's chief counsel Alan Garten calls the allegations "unsubstantiated" and "reckless", and says that Simpson was mainly referring to properties to which Trump licensed his name. Democratic committee member [[Jim Himes]] says that Simpson "did not provide evidence and I think that's an important point. He made allegations."<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-russia-fusion/possible-money-laundering-alleged-in-sales-of-trump-properties-rep-schiff-idUSKBN1F727X |title=Sales of Trump properties suggestive of money-laundering: researcher|date=January 18, 2018 |website=[[Reuters]]|access-date=April 11, 2018| last1=Landay|first1=Jonathan|last2=Strobel|first2=Warren}}</ref> * '''January 19''': ** German periodical ''[[Manager Magazin]]'' reports that Deutsche Bank has presented to Germany's financial authority, [[Federal Financial Supervisory Authority|BaFin]], evidence of "suspicious money transfers" by Kushner; this information is due to be handed to Mueller.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/deutsche-bank-investigating-jared-kushner-his-companies-for-suspicious-money-transfers/ar-AAuT87P |title=Deutsche Bank Investigating Jared Kushner, His Companies For Suspicious Money Transfers |publisher=International Business Times/Yahoo |date=January 19, 2018|last=Radesh|first=Sundeep Kavanal}}</ref> Deutsche Bank denies the report on January 22 and announces that it is taking legal action.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-deutsche-bank-report/deutsche-bank-denies-manager-magazin-report-on-kushner-idUSKBN1FB1SG |title=Deutsche Bank denies Manager Magazin report on Kushner |date=January 23, 2018 |website=Reuters|author=Reuters Staff}}</ref> ** House Republicans call for the release of a classified [[Nunes memo|memo authored by Nunes]] alleging [[Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act|FISA]] abuses during the 2016 election.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://thehill.com/policy/national-security/369721-gop-reps-demand-release-of-shocking-surveillance-memo |title=GOP reps demand release of 'shocking' surveillance memo |publisher=The Hill |date=January 19, 2018|last=Easley|first=Jonathan}}</ref> Nunes has repeatedly refused to share his concerns with the FBI, even after repeated requests by 