 Memo Rebutting Republican Claims |last1=Shear |first=Michael D. |last2=Fandos |first2=Nicholas |date=February 9, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=February 10, 2018 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> * '''February 12''': ** Senator [[Ron Wyden]] (D-OR), ranking member on the [[Senate Finance Committee]], asks the Treasury Department for documentation related to Trump's 2008 sale of an uninhabitable [[Maison de L'Amitie|Palm Beach mansion]] to Russian oligarch [[Dmitry Rybolovlev]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/politics-government/congress/article199726004.html |title=A Russian oligarch bought a mansion from Trump. A senator wants details on the deal. |work=mcclatchydc|access-date=February 13, 2018 |language=en|date=February 12, 2018|last=Rothacker|first=Rick}}</ref> ** ''Foreign Policy'' reports that [[FTI Consulting]] has had investigators "traveling the globe" for the past six months trying to verify parts of the Steele dossier. ''BuzzFeed'' hired FTI Consulting to help in their defense against the libel suit filed by Aleksej Gubarev in February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former Senior FBI Official Is Leading BuzzFeed’s Effort to Verify Trump Dossier|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/02/12/former-senior-fbi-official-is-leading-buzzfeeds-effort-to-verify-trump-dossier/|website=[[Foreign Policy]]|date=February 12, 2018|access-date=August 21, 2018|last=Winter|first=Jana|author-link=Jana Winter}}</ref> ** Russia threatens to block YouTube and [[Instagram]] if they do not take down videos and photos related to Deripaska that were posted by Navalny and Vashukevich.<ref>{{cite web|title=Russia Threatens to Block YouTube and Instagram, After Complaints From an Oligarch|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/12/world/europe/russia-youtube-instagram-navalny.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=February 12, 2018|access-date=September 3, 2018|last1=Luxmoore|first1=Matthew|first2=Daisuke|last2=Wakabayashi}}</ref> (see [[Media freedom