ele dossier subpoenas|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/house/401193-gop-chairman-set-to-issue-steele-dossier-subpoenas|website=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=August 9, 2018|access-date=August 12, 2018|last=Beavers|first=Olivia}}</ref> * '''August 10''': ** Judge Howell rules Andrew Miller is in [[contempt of court]] for refusing to appear before one of Mueller's grand juries. Howell [[Stay of proceedings|stays]] the contempt order to allow an appeal to proceed. After the closed hearing, Miller's lawyer Paul Kamenar says he asked the court for the contempt ruling so that he can file an appeal challenging the legality of the Mueller investigation.<ref name=JudgeHoldsRogerStoneWapo20180810>{{cite web|title=Judge holds Roger Stone associate in contempt for refusing to testify in Russia investigation|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/witness-in-mueller-probe-refuses-to-appear-before-grand-jury/2018/08/10/73e27130-9ca4-11e8-843b-36e177f3081c_story.html|website=[[The Washington Post]]|date=August 10, 2018|access-date=August 10, 2018|last1=Hsu|first1=Spencer S.|last2=Barrett|first2=Devlin}}</ref> ** Davis appears before one of Mueller's grand juries.<ref name=LifelongPoliticalScrapperNYT20180810>{{cite web|title=A Lifelong Political Scrapper, Roger Stone Is Fighting for His Own Legal Future|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/10/us/politics/roger-stone-russia-investigation.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=August 10, 2018|access-date=August 11, 2018|last1=Feuer|first1=Alan|last2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|author-link2=Maggie Haberman}}</ref> ** [[Randy Credico]]'s lawyer says Credico is scheduled to appear before Mueller's grand jury on September 7.<ref name=LifelongPoliticalScrapperNYT20180810 /> ** DNC lawyers use Twitter to serve WikiLeaks with the [[Democratic National Committee v. Russian Federation|lawsuit it filed in April]].<ref>{{cite web|title=WikiLeaks hit with DNC lawsuit — over Twitter|url=http://thehill.com/policy/technology/401324-wikileaks-hit-with-dnc-lawsuit-over-twitter|website=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=August 10, 2018|access-date=August 12, 2018|last=Bowden|first=John}}</ref> * '''August 13''': ** FBI Deputy Director [[David Bowdich]] overrules the recommendation of the [[Office of Professional Responsibility]] (OPR) and fires FBI agent [[Peter Strzok]] for violating bureau policies. The OPR had recommended demotion and a 60-day suspension. The firing contradicts FBI Director [[Christopher A. Wray|Christopher Wray]]'s assurances to Congress that the FBI would follow its regular processes.<ref>{{cite web|title=F.B.I. Agent Peter Strzok, Who Criticized Trump in Texts, Is Fired|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/13/us/politics/peter-strzok-fired-fbi.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=August 13, 2018|access-date=August 13, 2018|last1=Goldman|first1=Adam|last2=Schmidt|first2=Michael S.|author-link1=Adam Goldman|author-link2=Michael S. Schmidt}}</ref> Trump heralds the firing on Twitter.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1029036065158557701|author=Donald J Trump|author-link=Donald Trump|user=realDonaldTrump|date=August 13, 2018|access-date=August 13, 2018|title=Agent Peter Strzok was just fired from the FBI - finally. The list of bad players in the FBI & DOJ gets longer & longer. Based on the fact that Strzok was in charge of the Witch Hunt, will it be dropped? It is a total Hoax. No Collusion, No Obstruction - I just fight back!}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|number=1029037282676957185|author=Donald J Trump|author-link=Donald Trump|user=realDonaldTrump|date=August 13, 2018|access-date=August 13, 2018|title=Just fired Agent Strzok, formerly of the FBI, was in charge of the Crooked Hillary Clinton sham investigation. It was a total fraud on the American public and should be properly redone!}}</ref> ** Judge [[Dabney Friedrich|Friedrich]] rules that Mueller's appointment was constitutional. The ruling is in response to a motion lawyers for [[Concord Management and Consulting]] made on